Veln is a FreeBSD virtualization management CLI that provides a user-friendly
interface for managing bhyve virtual machines.

Features:
- VM lifecycle management (create, start, stop, destroy)
- ZFS integration with snapshots, clones, and ZVOLs
- ISO image management with automatic downloads
- VM templates for rapid deployment
- Cloud-init integration for automated guest configuration
- REST API server for remote management
- VNC console support
- UUID support for VM identification
- Resource monitoring with safety buffers
- Bhyve requirement checking

Veln abstracts the complexity of bhyve command-line arguments while providing
access to advanced features. It supports both TAP+bridge networking for simple
setups and VALE for high-performance networking.

